abstract = {The article discusses the directions and trends in the development of digitization and data analysis in industrial applications. Particular attention was paid to the issue of digitization of production, which gradually enters all layers of the production system, starting from the layer of investment management, production planning, control, communication up to the level of intelligent object devices. Digitization is one of the basic pillars of the Industry 4.0 initiative and at the same time a response to the growing requirements of the global industry by creating digital models of processes implemented in production companies and conducting simulations in order to improve and optimize them. Therefore, special attention was paid to the possibility of using modern tools supporting the registration of digital data and their quick processing, which include AR technology and artificial intelligence.}
